## CSRD ↔ GRI Overlap Resolution Policy

For this period, `csrd_primary` is applied to all shared metric_keys between CSRD and GRI.
This means:
- CSRD ESRS disclosures are self-contained and authoritative.
- GRI sections contain a cross-reference paragraph pointing to the CSRD disclosure.
- No independent GRI narrative is drafted for `csrd_primary` metrics.
- Metrics with `both_required` (e.g. SASB sector-specific items) are disclosed independently.

Items marked `NEEDS_HUMAN_DECISION` ({{ summary.needs_human_decision }} total) require
the sustainability team to set overlap_resolution in esg_framework_mappings before
the next gap-detector run.

